So, you want to tell me
why you were sleeping

03:05.912 --> 03:07.413
In the backseat of a car
at school?

03:07.480 --> 03:08.712
Well, it was either there

03:08.779 --> 03:10.413
Or that smelly couch
in the teacher's lounge.

03:10.481 --> 03:11.880
I can't believe you sit
on that thing.

03:11.947 --> 03:13.947
For the record,
i don't go near that thing.

03:14.013 --> 03:15.247
So, tell me
where you live

03:15.314 --> 03:17.419
Because i'm pretty sure
it's not in shop class.

03:18.881 --> 03:20.814
I live in a foster home.

03:23.149 --> 03:24.915
Okay.

03:24.982 --> 03:26.249
Well,
give me your number.

03:26.316 --> 03:28.483
I'm gonna need to speak
with your foster parents.

03:28.550 --> 03:32.484
Hell no. Please.
That'll just make it worse.

03:32.550 --> 03:35.250
This is none
of your business, okay?

03:35.318 --> 03:37.384
Sam, if there's a problem
at home, tell me.

03:37.451 --> 03:38.684
I can get you some help.

03:38.750 --> 03:40.151
There's not a problem.

03:40.219 --> 03:41.985
This is one of the better
fosteromes i've been in.

03:42.052 --> 03:43.618
The others were...

03:43.685 --> 03:46.751
Not so good.

03:46.819 --> 03:49.320
So it's just a little crowded.
It's okay.

03:49.386 --> 03:50.487
It's not okay, sam.

03:50.553 --> 03:52.320
Is there anybody
that was worried

03:52.387 --> 03:54.287
That you didn't come home
last night?

03:54.354 --> 03:56.753
You don't get it.

03:56.820 --> 03:58.653
Nobody cares.

03:58.721 --> 04:00.032
It's kind of like
being invisible.

04:00.067 --> 04:02.688
Cash their checks, i don't get
slapped around. That's the deal.

04:02.754 --> 04:04.621
And it's a pretty
good deal.

04:04.689 --> 04:06.123
So don't screw this up
for me.

04:06.189 --> 04:08.991
Sam, i can't just pretend
like this didn't happen.

04:09.026 --> 04:10.456
You're 15 years old.

04:10.492 --> 04:12.057
There has to be something
better for you.

04:12.124 --> 04:15.023
You seem nice,
but i'm not your girl.

04:15.090 --> 04:18.623
I'm not anybody's girl.
It happens.

04:18.690 --> 04:19.757
Sam!

04:23.540 --> 04:25.940
Millie: look who it is -
The world's best boss.

04:26.007 --> 04:28.274
And what are you
buttering me up for?

04:28.341 --> 04:30.441
Nothing.
We just have lots to do.

04:30.508 --> 04:33.275
Millie,
i love you dearly,

04:33.341 --> 04:36.479
But you realize we are
standing in a clothing store

04:36.515 --> 04:39.643
<i>That has no clothes
in it,</i>

04:39.710 --> 04:41.843
And i am fresh out
of ideas.

04:41.909 --> 04:44.143
<i>Are you sure about that?</i>

04:45.559 --> 04:47.076
What is that?

04:47.144 --> 04:49.077
I wrote down a list
of ideas.

04:49.144 --> 04:51.498
And then you covered them
with a sheet?

04:51.533 --> 04:52.838
Yeah, that was more
for effect.

04:52.874 --> 04:54.911
I've always wanted to pull
a sheet off something

04:54.978 --> 04:56.078
And say "voil?"

04:56.145 --> 04:58.045
All right, well,
now's your big chance.

04:59.812 --> 05:01.621
"Go skydiving"?

05:01.656 --> 05:03.380
You didn't let me
say "voil?"

05:03.446 --> 05:05.912
I'm sorry.
But, look.

05:05.980 --> 05:08.414
Skydiving sounds
really fun and all,

05:08.481 --> 05:12.014
But how is it gonna help
this company?

05:12.081 --> 05:14.464
Well, maybe before
you can heal the company,

05:14.499 --> 05:16.848
You have to heal your soul
a little first.

05:18.628 --> 05:20.483
"Ride a motorcycle.

05:20.549 --> 05:23.516
"Learn to speak french.

05:23.584 --> 05:25.916
"Get drunk at oktoberfest.

05:25.983 --> 05:28.783
Watch every
james bond movie."

05:31.118 --> 05:34.618
Millie, why do these
all sound so familiar?

05:34.686 --> 05:36.085
Because they're all
your ideas.

05:36.152 --> 05:38.219
You're always talking
about stuff you wanted to try,

05:38.286 --> 05:39.952
And victoria either said
they were stupid

05:40.020 --> 05:41.320
Or you were too busy.

05:41.387 --> 05:42.919
So while she was
telling me

05:42.986 --> 05:44.953
I couldn't do any
of these things...

05:45.020 --> 05:47.886
I was writing them down
so someday you could.

05:47.954 --> 05:50.688
Welcome to someday,
brooke davis.

05:50.755 --> 05:53.695
* maybe they had it made
somehow *

05:53.731 --> 05:56.176
* living for there and then *

05:56.211 --> 05:58.622
* under a psychedelic spell *

05:58.690 --> 06:00.123
Thank you.

06:00.189 --> 06:01.822
So, you gonna show
me something?

06:01.889 --> 06:05.139
* still they had so much
to tell *

06:05.175 --> 06:08.391
* whatever happens
to the dreamers *

06:09.636 --> 06:10.790
Hey, man.
What the hell was that?

06:10.858 --> 06:12.292
That was game.

06:12.358 --> 06:13.425
We not working
on your jumper,

06:13.492 --> 06:14.525
So why would you pull up
like that?

06:14.592 --> 06:15.601
You cut off the lane.

06:15.636 --> 06:17.358
So, don't let me cut
the lane off, then.

06:17.426 --> 06:19.259
What if your jumper
not falling that day?

06:19.326 --> 06:21.126
So, what? You too scared
to get physical?

06:21.192 --> 06:23.403
You want physical?
Yeah.

06:24.527 --> 06:26.993
* it's only when they close
their eyes *

06:27.060 --> 06:29.761
Hoo-Hoo. That's what i'm talking
about, baby.

06:29.827 --> 06:31.028
Whoo!

06:31.094 --> 06:32.961
You're doing great, honey.

06:33.028 --> 06:34.495
Thanks.Thanks.

06:36.562 --> 06:38.296
Just check the ball.

06:51.997 --> 06:54.964
* i love you, i do *

06:59.333 --> 07:02.999
* nothing's ever been
this way before *

07:04.817 --> 07:09.000
* a dream is just a dream
and nothing more *

07:10.959 --> 07:14.868
* nothing's ever been
